RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 6F All Weather Track CR: 85. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EMERALD MAGIC unhurried in the early stages, saved ground to the quarter marker while not far back, tipped three wide at the top of the lane, came within aim inside of the furlong marker, overtook the top pair inside of the sixteenth-marker and kicked clear in the late stages. GENTLEMAN'S SECRET forwardly placed in the early stages, pressed the moderate pace while on a hold to the turn, took a narrow lead nearing the quarter marker, battled with HULA KING to mid-stretch, could not keep pace with EMERALD MAGIC in the late stages and just held for place. HULA KING broke alertly and assumed command in the early going, contested the moderate pace with GENTLEMAN'S SECRET to the turn, battled with that rival to the furlong grounds, gave way in deep stretch, was just edged for place and held for show in the final strides. CONTINENTAL UNION away a step slowly, recovered to be just off of the pace nearing the turn while outside of rivals, chased the moderate pace three wide on the turn, swung five wide for the drive and was outkicked in the final furlong. THAT'S BIND BABE close up to the early pace, lost ground while two wide on the turn, swung four wide for the drive and lacked a late rally.

ENTRY.NAME: That's Bind Babe
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up early,lost ground 2wide turn,4wide upper,no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Continental Union
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slowly,chased 3wide turn,5wide upper,outkicked stretch

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HARCYN sent after an alert beginning, set moderate fractions to the turn, in hand to the quarter marker, quickened in upper stretch and extended the lead nearing the furlong grounds, given one reminder tap of the crop inside of the furlong pole and was hand urged to the wire. STRUT ON LOUIE away a step slowly, encountered early traffic behind RACHEL'S COACH, angled to the inside to stalk the moderate pace to the turn, came in tight while advancing nearing the quarter marker, swung two wide for the drive, was no match for HARCYN in the stretch run but stayed on to be second best in the end. RACHEL'S COACH stalked the early pace, raced outside of rivals into the turn, came four wide into the drive, was outkicked in the final furlong and was clear for third in the end. STRENGTH OF AUTISM showed early speed and raced close up to the early pace, kept attendance to HARCYN through moderate fractions while three wide nearing the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 6F All Weather Track CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAD BOD crowded EASTER TRIBUTE a bit at the start, was asked to show early speed and dictated terms to the turn, set a pressured pace to the quarter marker, battled with GALLAND DE BESOS to mid-stretch, repelled that foe inside of the furlong marker and drew away in the final sixteenth. GALLAND DE BESOS tracked the moderate early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, confronted DAD BOD in upper stretch, battled with that foe to the furlong pole, was repelled inside of the furlong grounds and held for place in the final stages. EASTER TRIBUTE crowded by DAD BOD at the start and was away a step slowly, unhurried to the turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker, ran evenly to mid-stretch, finished well in deep stretch and was clear for show in the late stages. POLLO D'ORO prominent in the early going, pressed the moderate pace to the quarter marker, lost ground in upper stretch and faded in the final furlong. WAY TOO HOT allowed to settle, steadied in traffic behind the tiring WAKES AND WEDDINGS midway through the turn, raced two wide into the drive and did not threaten late. WAKES AND WEDDINGS close up to the early pace, chased four wide into the turn, impeded WAY TOO HOT when attempting to slip to the rail midway through the turn, outrun approaching the quarter marker and tired in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M All Weather Track CR: 89. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: WORK TO LIVE broke alertly and assumed command in the early going, set moderate fractions while prompted through the half-mile marker, drew clear along the far turn, drew off approaching the furlong pole and was hand urged to the finish as much the best. MISS MAIA allowed to settle while not far back in the early going, saved ground into the backstretch run, stalked the moderate pace to the quarter marker, was no match for WORK TO LIVE in the stretch run and held well for place in the late stages. SHE'S A BIT SASSY bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, rushed up to be forwardly placed into the first turn, prompted the moderate pace to the second turn, could not keep pace with WORK TO LIVE, weakened in the drive and was outfinished for place, while clear in the end for show. UNWHIRLED unhurried in the early stages, well positioned while two wide through the backstretch run, asked for run nearing the quarter marker and did not produce a late rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,set pace,well rated,clear 1/4,drew off,handily,much best

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUST MAKER tracked the decent early pace to the turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker, advanced in upper stretch, responded to steady urging, came within aim of ABOVE THE STARS inside of the furlong marker, overtook that rival in deep stretch and powered home in the final stages. ABOVE THE STARS broke alertly, contested the early pace with TOM'S CHARM, set a pressured pace while outside of that rival to the quarter marker, shook free in upper stretch and drew clear nearing the furlong pole, could not hold off DUST MAKER in deep stretch and was second best in the end. SHEZA QUEEN BEE broke in then hit the gate at the start and was away slowly, chased the pace to the turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, was not able to impact the top two in deep stretch but finished well and was up for show in the final strides. CUTE RENEGADE chased the decent early pace, raced three wide into the turn, swung four wide into the drive, was gaining in the final furlong and just missed for third. TOM'S CHARM engaged with ABOVE THE STARS in the early stages and dueled for pace duties with that rival to the turn, disputed the pace to the quarter marker, lost position in upper stretch and faded in the drive. ZARAGOZA slow into stride early on and was unhurried, raced two wide along the turn, swung five wide for the drive and did not factor in the late stages. RED HARBOR chased the early pace from the inside, well positioned approaching the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch and tired.

JAYCEE hustled leaving the break and carved the early fractions, set the pace off of the rail to the quarter marker, was set down for the drive, overtaken by MISS ARROWHEAD inside of the furlong pole and held well in the final stages to be second best. RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY THIRSTY broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set decent fractions while well handled to the quarter marker, extended the lead nearing the furlong marker and drew away in the late stages. NIGHT CRUISER allowed to settle early on, saved ground on the turn, was not able to impact the winner in deep stretch but finished well in the final furlong and was up for place in the final strides. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Races Where Entered For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered For The Optional Claiming Price).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SALLY'S SASSY allowed to settle in the early stages, raced two wide on the turn, mounted a four wide rally in upper stretch, closed fast inside of the furlong marker, confronted ROUSING JEWEL in deep stretch, traded bumps with that rival in the final strides and determinedly won the nod on the wire. ROUSING JEWEL tracked the early pace, advanced two wide on the turn, came within aim nearing the furlong pole, closed determinedly to confront ELECTRIC LETTUCE in deep stretch, held a brief lead before being confronted by SALLY'S SASSY, exchanged bumps with that foe in the final strides and was gamely bested, while clear of the rest. ELECTRIC LETTUCE prominent in the early stages and pressed the decent pace to the turn, kept close attendance to KETANJI to the quarter marker, overtook that foe in upper stretch, assumed command and led to inside of the furlong marker, could not hold off the closing top pair in deep stretch and was well clear in the end for third. MAJESTIC OOPS allowed to settle in the early going, raced three wide on the turn, swung four wide for the drive and did not factor in the late stages. KETANJI broke alertly and showed good early speed, set a pressured pace to the turn, shook free nearing the quarter marker, could not hold off ELECTRIC LETTUCE in upper stretch, chased that rival to the furlong grounds and weakened late. THREAD COUNT bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered to chase the decent early pace to the turn, was asked for run nearing the quarter marker and came up empty in the drive. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE BUMPING IN DEEP STRETCH INVOLVING SALLY'S SASSY AND ROUSING JEWEL. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS DETERMINED THERE WAS MUTUAL BUMPING BETWEEN THE TWO RUNNERS AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 88. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. (One win for $20,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXPLAIN THIS AUDIT brushed the gate at the break and was off a step slow, had only one beat early, idled behind the field while patiently waiting for racing room through the far turn, was still last with three-sixteenths to run, found a hole passing the eighth pole and surged ahead when clear. BIG SPIN unhurried early, remained near the rear of the field through the first half of the race, began a forward move while four wide heading into the far turn, came under a ride with three furlongs to run, entered the stretch on the far outside of a six-horse fan, closed stoutly down the middle of the track to gain the place. ASANO'S BACK broke well and had good position into the first turn, ceded the lead to AUSPICIOUS STYLE and backed off the pace for the backstretch run, got held up behind horses on the far turn but responded to strong handling once clear and finished well but could not threaten the top pair. L'ENFANT DIT was keen to go from the break and fought the rider into the clubhouse turn, settled well behind the pace racing between horses down the backstretch, was full of run through the turn and into the stretch while stuck behind horses, swung out to the five path and closed with a rush when finally clear. RIO KING reserved well off the early pace, stayed to the inside throughout, had a difficult trip from the far turn to the wire, but did finish with some interest when able to get clear in deep stretch. GABBY HAYES got away from the gate in good order, looked intent on challenging for the early lead, then backed off the early pace, was keen to go and the moved to a stalking position to the outside of AUSPCIOUS STYLE, engaged at the head of the stretch, held a very brief lead then was outfinished from all sides just inside the furlong grounds. YOU KIDDING ME broke alertly, gained the inside position and was content to race mid-pack early, ducked to the inside for clear running near the eleven-sixteenths pole, made steady forward progress after that, was in striking position by the quarter pole while awaiting some racing room, got clear run past the three-sixteenths pole but was outfinished by a host of closers, finishing somewhat one-paced. AUSPICIOUS STYLE aggressive from the break and able to clear the field and grab the lead and inside position going into the clubhouse turn, held sway to the quarter pole then came under pressure, hung in there for a furlong but was done with an eighth of a mile to run and faded. SPROSTON content to track the pace from a three wide position, launched an early bid from the half-mile pole, loomed a threat at the head of the stretch but stalled and was unable to keep up down the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside trip, awaited room 1/4, no late bid, one-paced late
